{"type":"text","timestamp":1773439991104,"sessionID":"ses_316be8edcffeznA8v4atF4wsHM","part":{"id":"prt_ce9423474002pmot496cFjISyN","sessionID":"ses_316be8edcffeznA8v4atF4wsHM","messageID":"msg_ce94228f4001ZECOrMYAVD9uDL","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement the TOON (Token-Optimized Output Notation) `--output toon` format across all commands in the wombo-combo CLI tool. This is a compact, pipe-delimited output format designed for LLM agent consumption that reduces token count by 60%+ compared to JSON.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Feature branch: `feature/toon-output`\n- Must be a third output format alongside `text` and `json` (`--output toon`)\n- Must reduce token count by at least 60% compared to JSON output\n- Key abbreviations must be consistent across all commands\n- Must include a legend/schema command (`woco describe --output toon`)\n- Pipe-delimited fields, single-char status codes, abbreviated enums\n- Must auto-detect when an agent is consuming output (heuristic or explicit flag via `WOMBO_OUTPUT=toon` env var)\n- Do NOT sacrifice parseability for compactness\n- Do NOT use ambiguous abbreviations\n- Use conventional commits with scope `toon-output`\n- Commit after each logical unit of work\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `tasks/` directory\n- Run `bun run build` to verify after all changes\n- Use `bun dev` (not global `wombo` binary) for testing\n- Always use `portless run` when starting any server\n\n## Discoveries\n\n**The TOON infrastructure is ALREADY EXTENSIVELY BUILT.** After thorough codebase exploration, I found:\n\n1. **Core TOON modules already exist and are complete:**\n   - `src/lib/toon-spec.ts` — Full spec with encode/decode maps for status (BL/PL/IP/BK/IR/DN/CN), priority (C/H/M/L/W), difficulty (T/E/M/H/V), duration encoding, boolean encoding, array encoding, and per-command field definitions for ALL commands\n   - `src/lib/toon.ts` — Complete renderers for: `renderTasksList`, `renderTaskShow`, `renderStatus`, `renderVerify`, `renderHistoryList`, `renderHistoryDetail`, `renderTasksCheck`, `renderAbort`, `renderCleanup`, `renderMerge`, `renderRetry`, `renderLogs`, `renderLaunchDryRun`, `renderGraph`, `renderVerifyResults`, `renderGeneric`\n   - `src/lib/output.ts` — `OutputFormat` type already includes `\"toon\"`, `resolveOutputFormat()` handles `\"toon\"`, `output()` function accepts optional `toonRenderer` parameter, `outputError()` and `outputMessage()` handle TOON format\n\n2. **All commands already have TOON support integrated:**\n   - `tasks list` — Has TOON renderer callback using `renderTasksList`\n   - `tasks show` — Has TOON renderer callback using `renderTaskShow`\n   - `tasks check` — Has TOON renderer callback using `renderTasksCheck`\n   - `tasks graph` — Has TOON renderer, both in `output()` callback and direct `fmt === \"toon\"` check\n   - `status` — Has TOON renderer callback using `renderStatus`\n   - `abort` — Has TOON renderer callback using `renderAbort`\n   - `cleanup` — Has TOON renderer callback using `renderCleanup` (both dry-run and real)\n   - `history` — Has TOON renderer callbacks for both list and detail views\n   - `verify` — Has TOON renderer callback using `renderVerifyResults`\n   - `merge` — Has TOON renderer callbacks for both dry-run and real merge\n   - `retry` — Has TOON renderer callbacks for both dry-run and real retry\n   - `logs` — Has TOON renderer callback + follow mode TOON support\n   - `launch` — Has TOON renderer for dry-run via `renderLaunchDryRun`\n   - `describe --output toon` — Has full TOON legend via `renderToonLegend` and `buildToonSpec`\n\n3. **Commands using `outputMessage`/`outputError` get TOON for free** (these already handle toon format): `tasks add`, `tasks set-status`, `tasks set-priority`, `tasks set-difficulty`, `tasks archive`\n\n4. **The `index.ts` entry point already imports and uses TOON modules** — `buildToonSpec`, `renderToonLegend` are imported and used in the `describe` command handler.\n\n5. **Auto-detection is implemented** via `WOMBO_OUTPUT=toon` env var in `resolveOutputFormat()`.\n\n## Accomplished\n\n**Reading/analysis phase is complete.** Every relevant file has been read and analyzed. The conclusion is that **the TOON output feature appears to be fully implemented already.** \n\n**What remains to be done:**\n1. **Verify the build passes** — Run `bun run build` to confirm everything compiles\n2. **Assess if anything is actually missing** — The implementation looks comprehensive but should be verified against the spec requirements\n3. **If build passes and all constraints are met, the task may already be done** — just needs build verification\n4. **If there are gaps**, implement them (but from the analysis, no gaps were found)\n5. **Add tests if needed** (though the project has no test suite yet per AGENTS.md)\n6. **Update help text** to mention `--output toon` (currently help says `--output <fmt>` with \"text (default on TTY) or json (default when piped)\" — should mention `toon`)\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Core TOON implementation (already complete):\n- `src/lib/toon.ts` — All TOON renderers for every command\n- `src/lib/toon-spec.ts` — TOON format specification, encode/decode maps, field definitions, legend renderer\n- `src/lib/output.ts` — OutputFormat type, resolveOutputFormat(), output(), outputError(), outputMessage()\n\n### Entry point and routing:\n- `src/index.ts` — CLI arg parsing, command routing, `describe --output toon` handler\n\n### Commands with TOON support (all already integrated):\n- `src/commands/tasks/list.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/show.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/check.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/graph.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/add.ts` (via outputMessage)\n- `src/commands/tasks/set-status.ts` (via outputMessage)\n- `src/commands/tasks/set-priority.ts` (via outputMessage)\n- `src/commands/tasks/set-difficulty.ts` (via outputMessage)\n- `src/commands/tasks/archive.ts` (via outputMessage)\n- `src/commands/status.ts`\n- `src/commands/abort.ts`\n- `src/commands/cleanup.ts`\n- `src/commands/history.ts`\n- `src/commands/verify.ts`\n- `src/commands/merge.ts`\n- `src/commands/retry.ts`\n- `src/commands/logs.ts`\n- `src/commands/launch.ts`\n- `src/commands/resume.ts`\n\n### Project config:\n- `package.json` — Build scripts, dependencies\n- `AGENTS.md` — Development conventions\n- `tsconfig.json` — TypeScript config","time":{"start":1773439991103,"end":1773439991103}}}
