{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1773440145220,"sessionID":"ses_316bba7c1ffenLP0vTOciFexZp","part":{"id":"prt_ce9451743001YZ11zY17dT85q8","sessionID":"ses_316bba7c1ffenLP0vTOciFexZp","messageID":"msg_ce9450a25001dFe9Aac9kCRj1v","type":"step-start","snapshot":"697c9a4bc34d88e19c7d3a35afc34b7fb348f5e8"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773440186618,"sessionID":"ses_316bba7c1ffenLP0vTOciFexZp","part":{"id":"prt_ce9451743002PCK8mqK325kyxx","sessionID":"ses_316bba7c1ffenLP0vTOciFexZp","messageID":"msg_ce9450a25001dFe9Aac9kCRj1v","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement the TOON (Token-Optimized Output Notation) output format (`--output toon`) across all commands in the wombo-combo CLI tool. This is a compact, pipe-delimited output format designed for LLM agent consumption that reduces token count by 60%+ vs JSON.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Feature branch: `feature/toon-output`, base: `main`\n- Must be a third output format alongside text and json (`--output toon`)\n- Must reduce token count by at least 60% compared to JSON output\n- Key abbreviations must be consistent across all commands\n- Must include a legend/schema command (`woco describe --output toon`)\n- Pipe-delimited fields, single-char status codes, abbreviated enums\n- Must auto-detect when an agent is consuming output (heuristic or explicit flag via `WOMBO_OUTPUT=toon` env var)\n- Do NOT sacrifice parseability for compactness — agents must split on delimiters reliably\n- Do NOT use ambiguous abbreviations\n- Use conventional commits with scope `toon-output`\n- Commit after each logical unit of work\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `tasks/` directory\n- Run `bun run build` to verify after all changes\n- Always use `bun dev` not global `wombo` binary when testing\n- Use `portless run` when starting any server\n\n## Discoveries\n\n**The TOON feature is already substantially implemented.** After thorough code review, here's what exists:\n\n### Already Done:\n1. **`src/lib/output.ts`** — `OutputFormat` type already includes `\"toon\"`, `resolveOutputFormat()` handles `\"toon\"`, `output()` function accepts a `toonRenderer` callback, `outputError()` and `outputMessage()` handle toon format. `WOMBO_OUTPUT=toon` env var auto-detection is implemented.\n\n2. **`src/lib/toon-spec.ts`** — Complete TOON specification with all encode/decode mappings (status codes BL/PL/IP/BK/IR/DN/CN, priority codes C/H/M/L/W, difficulty codes T/E/M/H/V), duration encoding, boolean encoding, null handling, array encoding. `buildToonSpec()` and `renderToonLegend()` for `woco describe --output toon`. Per-command field specs (`TOON_COMMAND_SPECS`) covering: tasks list, tasks show, status, history, verify, abort, cleanup, merge, retry, logs, tasks graph, launch.\n\n3. **`src/lib/toon.ts`** — Complete renderer module with functions: `renderTasksList`, `renderTaskShow`, `renderStatus`, `renderVerify`, `renderHistoryList`, `renderHistoryDetail`, `renderTasksCheck`, `renderAbort`, `renderCleanup`, `renderMerge`, `renderRetry`, `renderLogs`, `renderLaunchDryRun`, `renderGraph`, `renderVerifyResults`, `renderGeneric` (fallback).\n\n4. **`src/index.ts`** — Already imports toon-spec, handles `--output toon` in arg parsing, `describe` command with `--output toon` support already implemented, `COMMAND_ALIASES` includes `d: \"describe\"`.\n\n5. **All command files** already pass `toonRenderer` callbacks to the `output()` function:\n   - `tasks/list.ts` ✅ (uses `renderTasksList`)\n   - `tasks/show.ts` ✅ (uses `renderTaskShow`)\n   - `tasks/check.ts` ✅ (uses `renderTasksCheck`)\n   - `tasks/graph.ts` ✅ (uses `renderGraph`)\n   - `status.ts` ✅ (uses `renderStatus`)\n   - `history.ts` ✅ (uses `renderHistoryList`/`renderHistoryDetail`)\n   - `abort.ts` ✅ (uses `renderAbort`)\n   - `cleanup.ts` ✅ (uses `renderCleanup`)\n   - `merge.ts` ✅ (uses `renderMerge`)\n   - `verify.ts` ✅ (uses `renderVerifyResults`)\n   - `retry.ts` ✅ (uses `renderRetry`)\n   - `logs.ts` ✅ (uses `renderLogs`, follow mode handles toon)\n   - `launch.ts` ✅ (uses `renderLaunchDryRun`)\n\n6. Commands using `outputMessage()` (which handles toon via `#MSG`): `tasks/add.ts`, `tasks/set-status.ts`, `tasks/set-priority.ts`, `tasks/set-difficulty.ts`, `tasks/archive.ts` — these simpler mutation commands emit messages, which is appropriate.\n\n### What May Still Need Doing:\n- **Run `bun run build`** to verify everything compiles without errors\n- **Verify the help text** in `cmdHelp()` mentions `toon` as an output format (currently line 465 says `--output <fmt>  Output format: text (default on TTY) or json (default when piped)` — should mention `toon`)\n- **Check if the `resume.ts` command** has proper toon output (it uses `outputError`/`outputMessage` which handle toon, but doesn't use the `output()` function with custom toon renderers for its primary data)\n- Review whether token reduction is actually 60%+ (may need a simple test)\n\n## Accomplished\n\n- **Completed**: Full codebase review of all command files, lib files, and index.ts to assess TOON implementation status\n- **In progress**: Nothing actively being modified yet — only reading/analysis phase completed\n- **Left to do**: \n  1. Create a plan (TodoWrite)\n  2. Update help text to mention `toon` format\n  3. Run `bun run build` to check for compilation errors\n  4. Fix any build errors\n  5. Potentially add any missing TOON coverage\n  6. Commit changes\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Core TOON infrastructure (already implemented):\n- `src/lib/toon.ts` — All TOON renderer functions\n- `src/lib/toon-spec.ts` — TOON format specification, encode/decode mappings, legend\n- `src/lib/output.ts` — Output format resolution, `output()`/`outputError()`/`outputMessage()` with toon support\n\n### CLI entry point:\n- `src/index.ts` — Arg parsing, command routing, describe command with toon support\n\n### Command files (all have toon support via callbacks):\n- `src/commands/tasks/list.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/show.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/check.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/graph.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/add.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/set-status.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/set-priority.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/set-difficulty.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/archive.ts`\n- `src/commands/status.ts`\n- `src/commands/history.ts`\n- `src/commands/abort.ts`\n- `src/commands/cleanup.ts`\n- `src/commands/merge.ts`\n- `src/commands/verify.ts`\n- `src/commands/retry.ts`\n- `src/commands/logs.ts`\n- `src/commands/launch.ts`\n- `src/commands/resume.ts`\n\n### Project config:\n- `package.json` — Build script: `bun run build`\n- `AGENTS.md` — Development conventions","time":{"start":1773440186616,"end":1773440186616}}}
