{"type":"text","timestamp":1773440286440,"sessionID":"ses_316bba7c1ffenLP0vTOciFexZp","part":{"id":"prt_ce9472046001o4GgIKEoV3U01u","sessionID":"ses_316bba7c1ffenLP0vTOciFexZp","messageID":"msg_ce947183b001D0gJOOABEIc4zV","type":"text","text":"All done. Here's a summary of the work completed on this branch:\n\n## Summary\n\nThe TOON output feature was **already substantially implemented** across the entire codebase by prior feature branches (`toon-wire-commands`, etc.). The only remaining gap was in the **CLI help text**, which didn't mention `toon` as an available output format.\n\n### What was done in this session:\n\n1. **Full codebase audit** — Verified all 15+ command files have proper TOON renderer callbacks wired into `output()`, and that `outputMessage()`/`outputError()` (used by simpler mutation commands) correctly handle toon format.\n\n2. **Confirmed `resume.ts` coverage** — This long-running operational command correctly uses `outputMessage()`/`outputError()` which handle toon. It doesn't need a custom toon renderer because its primary output is a live monitoring dashboard.\n\n3. **Updated CLI help text** (committed as `72f65d9`):\n   - `--output <fmt>` now reads: `text (default on TTY), json (default when piped), or toon (WOMBO_OUTPUT=toon)`\n   - `describe` command description updated to mention TOON legend support\n   - Added example: `woco describe --output toon  # emit TOON format legend/spec`\n\n4. **Build & typecheck pass** — Both `bun run typecheck` and `bun run build` succeed.","time":{"start":1773440286439,"end":1773440286439}}}
