{"type":"text","timestamp":1773440768872,"sessionID":"ses_316b2af3bffeauPmrTvOGPlpJe","part":{"id":"prt_ce94e2756001jE011YxkBx7ehC","sessionID":"ses_316b2af3bffeauPmrTvOGPlpJe","messageID":"msg_ce94e18b6001OmVN6JFXBH54sz","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement the TOON (Token-Optimized Output Notation) `--output toon` format across all commands in the wombo-combo CLI tool. This is a compact, pipe-delimited output format designed for LLM agent consumption that reduces token count by 60%+ compared to JSON.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- TOON must be a third output format alongside `text` and `json` (`--output toon`)\n- Must reduce token count by at least 60% compared to JSON output\n- Key abbreviations must be consistent across all commands\n- Must include a legend/schema command (`woco describe --output toon`) so agents can learn the format\n- Pipe-delimited fields, single-char status codes, abbreviated enums\n- Must auto-detect when an agent is consuming output (via `WOMBO_OUTPUT=toon` env var or explicit `--output toon` flag)\n- Do NOT sacrifice parseability for compactness — agents must be able to split on delimiters reliably\n- Do NOT use ambiguous abbreviations\n- Use conventional commits with scope `toon-output`\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `tasks/` directory\n- Always use `bun dev` (not the global binary) when testing\n- Run `bun run build` to verify everything works after changes\n\n## Discoveries\n\n- **The TOON feature is already fully implemented.** The branch `feature/toon-output` appears to have been created from `main` which already contains the merged work from `feature/toon-wire-commands`. All the TOON infrastructure is in place:\n  - `src/lib/toon-spec.ts` — Full TOON specification with encode/decode mappings for status (BL/PL/IP/BK/IR/DN/CN), priority (C/H/M/L/W), difficulty (T/E/M/H/V), duration encoding, boolean encoding, array encoding, and per-command field specs\n  - `src/lib/toon.ts` — Complete TOON renderers for all commands: `renderTasksList`, `renderTaskShow`, `renderStatus`, `renderVerify`, `renderHistoryList`, `renderHistoryDetail`, `renderTasksCheck`, `renderAbort`, `renderCleanup`, `renderMerge`, `renderRetry`, `renderLogs`, `renderLaunchDryRun`, `renderGraph`, `renderVerifyResults`, `renderGeneric`\n  - `src/lib/output.ts` — Output format infrastructure with `resolveOutputFormat()` supporting `text`/`json`/`toon`, `output()` function accepting optional `toonRenderer`, `outputError()` and `outputMessage()` with TOON-specific formatting\n  - All commands already pass TOON renderers to the `output()` function\n  - The `describe` command already handles `--output toon` to emit the TOON legend\n  - Help text already documents `--output toon`\n- The git log shows commits: `feat(toon-output): document toon format in CLI help text` and earlier `feat(toon-wire-commands): wire TOON renderers into all operational commands`\n- The working tree is clean with nothing to commit\n- The codebase uses Bun runtime, hand-rolled arg parsing (no CLI framework), ESM modules, TypeScript strict mode\n\n## Accomplished\n\n- **All work appears complete.** The TOON output format is fully implemented across all commands:\n  - ✅ Core TOON spec with encoding/decoding (`toon-spec.ts`)\n  - ✅ Per-command TOON renderers (`toon.ts`)\n  - ✅ Output infrastructure supporting `text`/`json`/`toon` (`output.ts`)\n  - ✅ All commands wired with TOON renderers (tasks list, show, check, archive, graph, add, set-status, set-priority, set-difficulty, status, verify, merge, retry, abort, cleanup, history, logs, launch)\n  - ✅ `woco describe --output toon` emits self-describing legend\n  - ✅ Auto-detection via `WOMBO_OUTPUT=toon` env var\n  - ✅ Help text updated\n  - ✅ CLI arg parsing supports `--output toon` / `-o toon`\n- **What remains:** Run `bun run build` to verify the build passes. If it passes, the task is done. If not, fix errors.\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n- `src/lib/toon-spec.ts` — TOON format specification, encode/decode mappings, field definitions per command, `buildToonSpec()`, `renderToonLegend()`\n- `src/lib/toon.ts` — All TOON renderers (737 lines), one per command output type\n- `src/lib/output.ts` — `OutputFormat` type, `resolveOutputFormat()`, `output()`, `outputError()`, `outputMessage()`, `filterFields()`\n- `src/index.ts` — CLI entry point, arg parsing, `--output` flag handling, `describe` command with TOON legend support\n- `src/commands/tasks/list.ts` — Tasks list with TOON renderer wired\n- `src/commands/tasks/show.ts` — Tasks show with TOON renderer wired\n- `src/commands/tasks/check.ts` — Tasks check with TOON renderer wired\n- `src/commands/tasks/archive.ts` — Tasks archive (uses `outputMessage`)\n- `src/commands/tasks/graph.ts` — Tasks graph with TOON renderer wired\n- `src/commands/tasks/add.ts` — Tasks add (uses `outputMessage`)\n- `src/commands/tasks/set-status.ts` — Set status (uses `outputMessage`)\n- `src/commands/tasks/set-priority.ts` — Set priority (uses `outputMessage`)\n- `src/commands/tasks/set-difficulty.ts` — Set difficulty (uses `outputMessage`)\n- `src/commands/status.ts` — Wave status with TOON renderer wired\n- `src/commands/verify.ts` — Verify with TOON renderer wired\n- `src/commands/merge.ts` — Merge with TOON renderer wired\n- `src/commands/retry.ts` — Retry with TOON renderer wired\n- `src/commands/abort.ts` — Abort with TOON renderer wired\n- `src/commands/cleanup.ts` — Cleanup with TOON renderer wired\n- `src/commands/history.ts` — History with TOON renderer wired\n- `src/commands/logs.ts` — Logs with TOON renderer wired\n- `src/commands/launch.ts` — Launch with TOON dry-run renderer wired\n- `src/commands/resume.ts` — Resume (uses `outputMessage`/`outputError`)\n- `src/lib/schema.ts` — Command schema registry for `describe`","time":{"start":1773440768871,"end":1773440768871}}}
